facts.fact_text: Czech Republic's industrial production rose by 3.8% year-on-year in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: Industrial production in the Czech Republic rose by 3.8% year-on-year in December 2025

facts.fact_text: The industrial production increase of 3.8% surpassed market expectations of 3.2%.
The industrial production growth slowed from 5.7% in the previous month.

evidences.evidence_text: albeit slowing from a more than three-year high of 5.7% in the previous month

facts.fact_text: Output growth slowed in manufacturing to 4.5% from 6.4% in November.

evidences.evidence_text: Output growth slowed in manufacturing (4.5% vs 6.4% in November)

facts.fact_text: Output tumbled for electricity, gas, steam, and air-conditioning supply by -2.6% compared to 2.6% previously.

evidences.evidence_text: output tumbled for electricity, gas, steam, and air-conditioning supply (-2.6% vs 2.6%)

facts.fact_text: Output in mining and quarrying rebounded to 6.3% from a 12.8% decline in November.

evidences.evidence_text: output in mining and quarrying rebounded notably to 6.3% from a 12.8% decline in November

facts.fact_text: On a monthly basis, industrial activity slowed to 0.4% in December from 2.4% in the prior month.

evidences.evidence_text: On a monthly basis, industrial activity slowed sharply to 0.4% in December from 2.4% in the prior month.

evidence.evidence_text: Industrial production in the Czech Republic rose by 3.8% year-on-year in December 2025
Output growth slowed in manufacturing (4.5% vs 6.4% in November)
output in mining and quarrying rebounded notably to 6.3% from a 12.8% decline in November
